# What is a Vector?
A vector is a directed line segment.
 ![Pasted image 20220103112334.png](data:image/png;base64,)
May have seen them as forces in physics.
![Pasted image 20220103112405.png](data:image/png;base64,)
# Notation:
Vectors can be notated as:
$$\vec{v} \,\, \text{or} \begin{bmatrix}A\\B\\C\end{bmatrix}
$$
# Vector Origin:
Floating vectors exist away from the origin:
![Pasted image 20220109132416.png](data:image/png;base64,)
There can also be vectors anchored at the origin:
![Pasted image 20220109132503.png](data:image/png;base64,)
